<br>
Until recently, beastlords had a level buffing spell that they used on their pets.  They would summon a green pet, and then buff the level.  They also have haste, sow, etc.<br>
<br>
Using Puppet Strings, a friend of mine used to charm a YK in WC, buff the level of it to 48th level or so, sow it, buff it, etc.  And then zone...<br>
<br>
Here you had this enraged bear, buffed to hell and gone, rampaging around WC.  Newbies screaming for help, training it to the druid rings, higher levels deciding to &quot;help out the poor lowbie&quot; and getting their butt handed to them because they didn't expect a YK to be dangerous.  OMG, it was funny. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eumerin>Eumerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 6:11:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Funniest ever</span><hr size=1> Not pet/mage related, but two things that I did hear last night.<br>
